    <div class="opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper  opener__text-start--1 opener__text-width--3 opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper--valign-center">

    
    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--vertical-rule -is-over-bg opener__hed--light opener__hed--small" >        Bedbugs, Rats and No Heat: How One Woman Endured a Decade of Neglect in New York’s Guardianship System
    </h1>

        <h2 class="opener__dek  -is-over-bg opener__dek--light" >        Judith Zbiegniewicz lived in squalor, yet every month, her legally appointed guardian was paid $450 from her bank account. She is one of the thousands of vulnerable New Yorkers left stranded by a system meant to protect them.
    </h2>
    
            <div class="article-meta-1  -is-over-bg article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <span class="name">Jake Pearson</span>, illustrations by <span class="name">Dominic Bodden</span>, special to <a href="https://www.propublica.org">ProPublica</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-03-07EST06:00">March 7, 6 a.m. EST</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

    
</div>
        
