    <div class="story-card__description">
                
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/how-one-woman-endured-decade-neglect-new-york-guardianship">
                                    Bedbugs, Rats and No Heat: How One Woman Endured a Decade of Neglect in New York’s Guardianship System
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Judith Zbiegniewicz lived in squalor, yet every month, her legally appointed guardian was paid $450 from her bank account. She is one of the thousands of vulnerable New Yorkers left stranded by a system meant to protect them.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <span class="name">Jake Pearson</span>, illustrations by <span class="name">Dominic Bodden</span>, special to <a href="https://www.propublica.org">ProPublica</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-03-07EST06:00">March 7, 6 a.m. EST</time>
        </p>

